&gt;     Hi Christian,
&gt;
&gt;     The ExtractorHTML class is used to add URIs to the queue waiting
&gt;     to be crawled. Since the title tag is not a valid URI it doesn&#39;t
&gt;     help to extract that tag in a modified version of that class. You
&gt;     could write your own writer class to store the title, and other
&gt;     tags to a file or database for that URI.
&gt;
&gt;     You can extract the title tag using a regular expression.
&gt;
&gt;     &quot;(?i)(&lt;title&gt;.*?&lt;/title&gt;)&quot;
&gt;
&gt;     As an example.
